{
  "texts": [
    "Example 1.2: Operators carrying gauge charges are non-genuineExamples of non-genuine operators are provided by operators which are not gauge invariant.",
    "Take the example of a U(1) gauge theory with a scalar field φ of gauge charge q.",
    "An insertion φ(x) of the corresponding local operator is not gauge invariant and hence not a well-defined genuine local operator.",
    "However, one can obtain a gauge-invariant configurationφ(x)exp iq ∞ x A,(8)by letting φ(x) lie at the end of a Wilson line operator of charge q.",
    "This configuration can be displayed diagrammatically as φ(x)W q = e iq A."
  ]
}